Jbb bhi apn code likhte hai uske saath hi apne ko suggestion aate rhte hai aur error rha to vo bhi dikhte rhte hai, to vo kiske vajah se rhte hai, inn threads ke vajah se hi

Those things run at the same time (i.e. Parallel) with thehelp of threads

WE can make threads using JAVA.
We have to make class and extend it with the class thread class
but this only will not make the things perfect
Within those classes define the method which needed to be worked parallel, but name that method as run (will tell you the reason)

then in main fx make their object and call the .start() method, this start method is parent class method which triggers the run method ,then the things goes properly.


class A extends Thread{
    public void run(){
        for(int i = 0 ; i < 100 ; i++){
            System.out.println("A kaa Hai");
            try {
                Thread.sleep(10);
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            }
        }
    }
}
public static void main(String[] args) {
        A obj1 = new A();
        B obj2 = new B();
        obj1.start();
        obj2.start();
    }

It prints properly which shows parallel processing.

Behind the scenes we have scheduler to give the time to threads to run.
We cannot set the priority but still we can say to our scheduler to that our priority, we have method to set priority to threads as setPriority() here we can pass Thread.MAX_PRIORITY which is 10 and the lowest priority is 1, by default it is 5 for all thread

But Still the threads are looked to be run like they are given more time, so one thing we can do to optimise make.
we need add some time after the execution of each thread by putting the sleep time (delay)


